returns_description.FMCReturnCode: If everything is ok, RC_SUCCESS is returned. In case another value is returned see FMCReturnCode.h for further reference.
returns_description.sc_pid_t: Returns an ID of an acyclic process (SC_ILLEGAL_PID is returned in case of error)
returns_description.LibRteDiagnosis&: Returns a reference to diagnosis handler sub-component
returns_description.IMemory&: Returns a reference to memory management interface. This is used for file access.
returns_description.LibRteMailboxManager&: A reference to a concrete Lib Rte Mailbox Manager
returns_description.LibRteProcessManager&: A reference to a concrete Lib Rte Process Manager
returns_description.LibRteNrtDriver&: A reference to a LibRteNrtDriver instance

argument_description.&processP0Handler: A reference to an abstract librte process handler.
argument_description.&processP1Handler: A reference to an abstract librte process handler.
argument_description.&processP2Handler: A reference to an abstract librte process handler.
argument_description.&moduleConfig: A reference to an abstract LibRteModuleConfig object.
argument_description.&communicationInformation:
A reference to an communicationInformation interface.
///   This is used to identify the protocol variant EtherCAT, PROFINET, ...
argument_description.&powerFailRTE: A reference to the power fail input/output signal of the RTE Controller
argument_description.&chipReset: A reference to the chip reset input/output signal of the RTE Controller
argument_description.&pdIrq: A reference to the process data irq input/output signal of the RTE Controller
argument_description.&mbxIrq: A reference to the mailbox irq input/output signal of the RTE Controller
argument_description.&memory: A reference to a memory management component for file access
argument_description.&deviceShutdown: A reference to device shutdown component (this interface informs when a shutdown will happen)
argument_description.&reset: A reference to a soft reset interface. This is used to perform a reset of the system
argument_description.&hardwareInformation: A reference to a hardware information interface. Used to get the hardware version.
argument_description.&firmwareVersionInformation: A reference to a firmware version information interface. Used to get the firmware version.
argument_description.*data: A pointer to a data buffer
